<p>"<b>Carmilla</b>" is a <a href="/wiki/Gothic_novel" title="Gothic novel" class="mw-redirect">Gothic</a> novella by <a href="/wiki/Sheridan_Le_Fanu" title="Sheridan Le Fanu">Joseph Sheridan Le Fanu</a>. First published in 1872, it tells the story of a young woman's susceptibility to the attentions of a female <a href="/wiki/Vampire" title="Vampire">vampire</a> named Carmilla. "Carmilla" predates <a href="/wiki/Bram_Stoker" title="Bram Stoker">Bram Stoker</a>'s <i><a href="/wiki/Dracula" title="Dracula">Dracula</a></i> by 25 years and has been adapted many times for cinema.</p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Carmilla.jpg" class="image" title="Illustration from The Dark Blue by D. H. Friston, 1872"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/80/Carmilla.jpg/180px-Carmilla.jpg" width="180" height="127" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Carmilla.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Illustration from <i>The Dark Blue</i> by <a href="/wiki/D._H._Friston" title="D. H. Friston" class="mw-redirect">D. H. Friston</a>, 1872</div>
</div>
</div>
